---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Documentation - Hovue"
  description="Complete documentation for Hovue - animated Vue icons library. Learn how to install, use, and customize animated icons in your Vue 3 and Nuxt 3 projects."
>
  <Navigation />
  
  <main style="padding-top: 80px; min-height: 100vh;">
    <div class="docs-container">
      <aside class="docs-sidebar">
        <h4>Getting Started</h4>
        <ul class="docs-nav">
          <li><a href="/docs" class="active">Introduction</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/installation">Installation</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/quick-start">Quick Start</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/nuxt">Nuxt Module</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Usage</h4>
        <ul class="docs-nav">
          <li><a href="/docs/usage">Basic Usage</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/props">Props & Options</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/animations">Animations</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/customization">Customization</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/typescript">TypeScript</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Components</h4>
        <ul class="docs-nav">
          <li><a href="/docs/icons/arrows">Arrows</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/icons/actions">Actions</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/icons/media">Media</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/icons/loaders">Loaders</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/icons">All Icons â†’</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Integrations</h4>
        <ul class="docs-nav">
          <li><a href="/docs/integrations/shadcn-vue">shadcn-vue</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/integrations/tailwind">Tailwind CSS</a></li>
          <li><a href="/docs/integrations/vite">Vite</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <article class="docs-content">
        <h1>Introduction</h1>
        <p>Hovue is a collection of beautifully crafted, animated icons for Vue 3 and Nuxt 3 applications. Each icon is built as a standalone Vue component with motion baked in.</p>

        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <p>Unlike static icon libraries, Hovue icons are designed with animation as a first-class citizen. Every icon includes thoughtfully crafted hover states, click feedback, and programmatic animation triggers.</p>

        <div class="docs-code">
          <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// Import individual icons</span><br>
          <span style="color: var(--purple);">import</span> &#123; <span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span>, <span style="color: var(--orange);">HoCheck</span> &#125; <span style="color: var(--purple);">from</span> <span style="color: var(--cyan);">'hovue'</span><br><br>
          <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// Use in your template</span><br>
          &lt;<span style="color: var(--orange);">HoArrowRight</span> <br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:size</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);">"24"</span><br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">color</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);">"currentColor"</span><br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">animation</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);">"slide"</span><br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">:animation-duration</span>=<span style="color: var(--cyan);">"300"</span><br>
          /&gt;
        </div>

        <h2>Nuxt Auto-Import</h2>
        <p>Using Nuxt? Icons are auto-imported automatically when you add the module.</p>

        <div class="docs-code">
          <span style="color: var(--text-muted);">// nuxt.config.ts</span><br>
          <span style="color: var(--purple);">export default</span> defineNuxtConfig(&#123;<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color: var(--pink);">modules</span>: [<span style="color: var(--cyan);">'hovue/nuxt'</span>]<br>
          &#125;)
        </div>

        <div class="docs-note">
          <strong>Note:</strong> This documentation is a work in progress. More content will be added soon!
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .docs-container {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
    gap: var(--spacing-xl);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .docs-sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px;
    height: fit-content;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .docs-sidebar h4 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .docs-sidebar h4:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .docs-nav {
    list-style: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .docs-nav li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .docs-nav a {
    display: block;
    padding: var(--spacing-sm) var(--spacing-md);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .docs-nav a:hover,
  .docs-nav a.active {
    background: var(--bg-dark);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .docs-nav a.active {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--primary);
    padding-left: calc(var(--spacing-md) - 2px);
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .docs-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .docs-content h1 {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .docs-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: var(--spacing-2xl) 0 var(--spacing-md);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .docs-content p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .docs-code {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }

  .docs-note {
    background: rgba(49, 151, 149, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(49, 151, 149, 0.2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .docs-container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    
    .docs-sidebar {
      position: relative;
      top: 0;
    }
  }
</style>

